Japanese Sold Net 101.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-11-30T23:53:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/japanese-sold-net-101-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended Nov. 25 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 101.4 billion yen ($1.3 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 13.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 12.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 100.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 259.1 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 134.8 billion yen in stocks, and sold 1163.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1557.6
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  